text: Faunus is an unincorporated community in Menominee County, in the U.S. state of Michigan. ==History== A post office was established at Faunus in 1896, and discontinued in 1908. The community was named after Faunus, a god in Roman mythology. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Menominee County, Michigan
title: Faunus, Michigan
